question: Explain quantum entanglement like I'm 5
response_a: Imagine you have two magic dice. If you roll a 6 on one, the other one shows a 6 too, instantly, no matter how far apart they are!
response_b: Quantum entanglement is a physical phenomenon that occurs when a group of particles are generated, interact, or share spatial proximity in a way such that the quantum state of each particle of the group cannot be described independently of the state of the others.
